A=====True=====21
This leader had ten soldiers escort Charles Maclean to Delagoa Bay, leading to 
accusations that Maclean was a spy. According to Donald Morris, this man executed seven 
thousand people for not being adequately grief-stricken after the death of his mother, 
Nandi. Nathaniel Isaacs was named the principal chief of Natal by this ruler but fled due to 
the anticipated massacre of white citizens by Dingane [[din-GAH-neh]]. An advocate for a 
short spear called an iklwa [[ICK-lwah]], for the point, who was this leader of the Zulu 
people?=====
Shaka Zulu =====